Package in.kncsolutions.dhelm.candlepattern.twoline

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BearishDojiStar
    According to literature the bearish doji star pattern is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with White body followed by a doji candle with atleast one shadows, where the body of doji candle is above the body of the previous White candle.
    BearishEngulfing
    According to literature the bearish engulfing pattern is a two line pattern composed of a a white candle followed by long candle with black body, where the body of the previous white candle is fully engulfed by the body of the following black candle.
    BearishHarami
    According to literature the bearish harami pattern is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with white body followed by a black candle, where the body of the black candle is fully engulfed by the body of the previous white candle.
    BearishHaramiCross
    According to literature the bearish harami cross pattern is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with white body followed by a doji candle with both shadows, where the doji candle along with both the shadows is fully engulfed by the body of the previous white candle.
    BearishKicking
    According to literature the bearish kicking pattern is a two line pattern composed of a a white marubozu candle followed by a black marubozu candle, where there is a gap in the downward direction at the opening in the black marubozu candle.
    BullishDojiStar
    According to literature the bullish doji star pattern is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with black body followed by a doji candle with atleast one shadows, where the body of doji candle is below the body of the previous black candle.
    BullishEngulfing
    According to literature the bullish engulfing pattern is a two line pattern composed of a a black candle followed by long candle with white body, where the body of the previous black candle is fully engulfed by the body of the following white candle.
    BullishHarami
    According to literature the bullish harami pattern is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with black body followed by a white candle, where the body of the white candle is fully engulfed by the body of the previous black candle.
    BullishHaramiCross
    According to literature the bullish harami cross pattern is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with black body followed by a doji candle with two shadows, where the doji candle with the shadows is fully engulfed by the body of the previous black candle.
    BullishKicking
    According to literature the bullish kicking pattern is a two line pattern composed of a a black marubozu candle followed by a white marubozu candle, where there is a gap in the opening in the white marubozu candle.
    DarkCloudCover
    According to literature the dark cloud cover is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with white body followed by a long black candle, where the open of the black candle is above or equal to the closing level of the white candle.
    DescendingHawk
    According to literature the descending hawk is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with white body followed by a white candle, where the body of the second candle is fully engulfed by the body of the previous candle.
    HomingPigeon
    According to literature the homing pigeon is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with black body followed by a black candle, where the body of the second candle is fully engulfed by the body of the previous candle.
    MatchingHigh
    According to literature the matching high is a two line pattern composed of a long White candle with no upper shadow followed by a White candle with no upper shadow, where the closing prices of both the candles are equal.
    MatchingLow
    According to literature the matching low is a two line pattern composed of a long black candle with no lower shadow followed by a black candle with no lower shadow, where the closing prices of both the candles are equal.
    PiercingLine
    According to literature the piercing line is a two line pattern composed of a long candle with black body followed by a long white candle, where the open of the white candle is below or equal to the closing level of the black candle.
